Anthony J. Bettencourt: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 11:15 PM ET
Software

Company Overview of Imperva, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Anthony J. Bettencourt  Chairman of the Board, Chief Executive Officer and President, Imperva, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 15 different industries.See Board Relationships56$6,041,470As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Anthony J. Bettencourt has been the Chief Executive Officer and President of Imperva Inc. since August 18, 2014 and serves as its Chairman since October 28, 2015. Mr. Bettencourt is a Co-Founder of National Banana, Inc. and serves as its Chief Executive Officer. He served as an Independent Advisor of Autonomy Corp. plc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of ZANTAZ at Cardiff Software, Inc. He served as Chief Executive Officer of Interwoven of Autonomy Corp. ... plc. He served as Senior Vice President of Special Projects at Autonomy Corporation plc. from 2006 to 2009. He is a Mentor for Global Social Benefit Incubator program of Santa Clara University. He has more than 25 years of senior management experience in a variety of high-tech companies. He is a Veteran of the enterprise search market. He served as the Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President at Coverity, Inc. since November 22, 2010. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Autonomy, Inc. Prior to joining Autonomy in 2005, he served as the Chief Executive Officer of Verity Inc., from March 6, 2003 to 2005 and also served as its President from September 1999 to September 2005. He joined Verity Inc., in July 1995 as Vice President of North American Sales. He served as Vice President of Worldwide Sales of Verity Inc., since 1996 and its Vice President of Worldwide Marketing until December 1996. He led the team that set the strategic direction and execution characteristics of Verity. He was responsible for developing key alliances with Netscape, Informix, Sybase, SCO and others. Mr. Bettencourt served as an Entrepreneur-In-Residence of U.S. Venture Partners. From December 1996 to September 1997, he served as an Officer of OnLive! Technologies. He rejoined Verity in September 1997 as Senior Vice President of Worldwide Sales and Product Marketing. He served as a Member of the Verity Management Team since 1995. He served senior management positions at Excelan, Quintus, Convergent Technologies and Altos Computer Systems. Mr. Bettencourt served as Vice President of Sales of Versant Object Technology from 1992 to June 1995 and also served as its Director of U.S. Sales from July 1990 to 1992. From December 1988 to July 1990, he served as Vice President of Sales of Rockwell CMC. He serves as the Chairman of Blinkx Inc. He served as the Non-Executive Chairman of Blinkx PLC from May 2007 to July 1, 2015. He has been a Director of Imperva Inc. since August 18, 2014. He serves as a Director of National Banana, Inc., NetBase Solutions, Inc., NextPage, Inc., Alameda County Community Food Bank and Formation Data Systems, Inc. He serves as a Member of Business Advisory Board at Velti Plc and Velti SA. He served as a Director of Proofpoint, Inc. from March 2012 to January 24, 2017. He served as Non Executive Director from May 2007 to March 31, 2016. He served as Director of Versant Corp. from January 2, 2012 to December 21, 2012. He served as a Director of Coverity, Inc. since November 22, 2010 and Anodot Ltd. until May 5, 2017. He served as a Director of Verity Inc., since September 1999. He served as a Director of Avolent, Inc. since October 31, 2006. He served as a Director of GoldenGate Software, Inc. He served as a Director of CrownPeak Technology, Inc. He serves on the Advisory board of Center for Science, Technology and Society of Santa Clara University. He is a Judge for the Tech Awards. In 2005, he was awarded the prestigious Ernst & Young Entrepreneur of the Year award for software and technology in the Silicon Valley. Mr. Bettencourt earned a B.A. in English from the Santa Clara University in 2006.Read Full Background




